    {
      "id": "1022832b_0628f76b",
      "file_path": "main/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/pap/main/startstop/PapDatabaseInitializer.java",
      "patchset_number": 6,
      "line": 70,
      "message": "I would like to solve Ajith's question with a ticket.   As this will require a bit more work (and testing) and passing another mandatory flag (\"-g\") similar to the \"-c\" for the config file which I was trying to avoid (source code should not make assumptions of location in an etc dir).   This will require OOM and CSIT changes, my main concern, especially when ported to *honolulu*.  \n\nIn terms of design approaches, I think the best approach would be something along the lines of preloadedPolicies (ie. preloadedGroups) in the config.json that can point to specific file locations to load groups as the current api capabilities, this way there would be no need for papdb.json or groups.json and all would be self-contained in the config.json.   If there's no values present in the preloadedGroups, PAP will start with no groups and will rely on user provision groups with REST API which may be a desired configuration.  \n\nIn any case, I suggest to do whatever we decide to design in this area under another ticket in istambul only.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 477,
        "name": "Jorge Hernandez",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "jorge.hernandez-herrero@att.com",
        "username": "jhh"
      },
      "updated": "2021-05-28 14:24:44.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "e0262ffe_d1933e6a",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "050b1453_f327404a",
      "file_path": "main/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/pap/main/startstop/PapDatabaseInitializer.java",
      "patchset_number": 6,
      "line": 70,
      "message": "can't we simply remove PapDb.json from the jar?  Of course, we'd have to add it to docker/csit and oom.  Is it a problem to add it to oom?  (Isn't that how we do the policy preloads for policy-api?)",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 811,
        "name": "Jim Hahn",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "jrh3@att.com",
        "username": "jrh3"
      },
      "updated": "2021-05-28 14:30:05.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "1022832b_0628f76b",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "608d9700_3e72744a",
      "file_path": "main/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/pap/main/startstop/PapDatabaseInitializer.java",
      "patchset_number": 6,
      "line": 70,
      "message": "Yes I agree - we should do the same that policy-api does. I think it used to have it in the jar also. It would be very useful to port this to Honolulu. A separate ticket is fine with me. Good for intern to work on.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 57,
        "name": "Pamela Dragosh",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "pd1248@att.com",
        "username": "pdragosh"
      },
      "updated": "2021-05-28 15:28:07.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "050b1453_f327404a",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "adc949dc_e1cf58fb",
      "file_path": "main/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/pap/main/startstop/PapDatabaseInitializer.java",
      "patchset_number": 6,
      "line": 70,
      "message": "Yes, policy-api supports both loading from a file or from jar with configuration in on single config file (first tries the file and then as a resource in jar if I recall correctly).\n\n@Jim, my hesitation is with Honolulu release only as it adds including OOM in maintenance. I have no issue with a larger solution in Istanbul.\n\nIn the scrum, there was also comments that liquibase may take over this group provisioning.  It wasn't clear to me, but if that is the case, it would undo this work.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 477,
        "name": "Jorge Hernandez",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "jorge.hernandez-herrero@att.com",
        "username": "jhh"
      },
      "updated": "2021-05-28 17:48:07.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "608d9700_3e72744a",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "413bd4b8_7eb85d65",
      "file_path": "main/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/pap/main/startstop/PapDatabaseInitializer.java",
      "patchset_number": 6,
      "line": 70,
      "message": "ah, so the changes you've made here mimic the behavior of policy-api.  In that case, I'm fine with this, particularly since it will likely go away anyhow.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 811,
        "name": "Jim Hahn",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "jrh3@att.com",
        "username": "jrh3"
      },
      "updated": "2021-05-28 18:41:06.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "adc949dc_e1cf58fb",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "1d3e2c1c_6f4d90a3",
      "file_path": "main/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/pap/main/startstop/PapDatabaseInitializer.java",
      "patchset_number": 6,
      "line": 70,
      "message": "This is different from policy-api, because there we use the information is part of the same config file that supplies all other configurations (rest, db, etc). And here we are adding one more file with a separate command line option. \nBut again I am okay with this change as anyway with liquibase introduction these things will change.",
      "author": {
